                    In order to determine the extent of biotrophic capacity in saprotrophic wood‐decay fungi and which systems may be useful models, we investigated the colonization of conifer seedling roots
                    in vitro
                    using an array of 201 basidiomycete wood‐decay fungi. Microtome sectioning, differential staining and fluorescence microscopy were used to visualize patterns of root colonization in microcosm systems containing
